todo.text:
[death:bashful]Oh.
Oh boy.
[death]This is embarassing.
You've reached a TODO item in the script that was never removed and never compeleted.
Sorry about that.  What would you like me to do?
todo.prompt: 'What would you like me to do?'

quick_end.text:
Well that was fast.
Game Over.
You've found the SPEEDRUN end!  How many others are there?  At least one.  Click to return to the main menu.

slow_reluctant_end.text:
After much delay you finally agree to follow death.
Your journey is entirely without small talk.
It's hard to tell if it's because death is annoyed or not.
Game Over.
You've found the SLOW end.  Click to return to menu.

return_to_life.text:
You wake up in your room uninjured and unsure if whatever you'd just experienced was grounded in reality.  You decide it must be Thursday because Thursday always has been kind of confusing.
Game Over.
You've found the LIFE end! Click to return to menu.

die_after_all.text:
You follow Death on an ambling path to what appears to be a processing facility.  Death, taxes, and bureaucracy are the only true universal constants it seems.  Death bids farewell and you enter for processing.
Game Over.
You've found the DIE AFTER ALL end! Click to return to menu.

hell_ending.text:
Hell isn't quite what you were expecting.  It's clean, warm, and not as dark as the mythos would have told.  You're making friends and things are stable.  What possibly could the future hold?
Game Over.
You've found the HELL end! Click to return to menu.

heaven_end.text:
Death leads you up an endless stairway, rising through clouds and sunrays.  When you reach the flat relief of the cloud that holds the high city, Death bids you well and departs.  You approach the gatekeeper and ask for passage.
Game Over.
You've found the HEAVEN end! Click to return to menu.

madness_end.text:
After centuries of wandering the abyss without human contact or internet cat pictures your mind begins to fray.
You descend into madness and your soul goes on to haunt an internet forum.
Game Over.
You've found the MADNESS end! Click to return to menu.

hello_reaper.text:
[death:no_eyes]Hello lost one.
  It's time to go.

end_just_do_it.text: [death]Honestly, your enthusiasm is pretty refreshing.  Let's go.

how_die.text:
[death:bashful]Honestly, I wasn't really paying attention.
[death]What were you doing just before now?

challenge_for_soul.text:
[death:no_eyes]Indeed, you may challenge me, but if you lose your soul will wander the abyssal plane for all of eternity.
Choose your game.

knife_monopoly.text:
[death:eyes_closed]Ah, another one tragically lost to knife monopoly -- a game you cannot win, but can lose less.
[death]It's a fitting metaphor for life.
[death:no_eyes]But now we must go.

streaming_on_twitch.text:
[death]I'm not quite sure what that means but it sounds ominous.  [death:bashful]Let that possibly be a lesson to you, I guess?
Anyway, [death:no_eyes]it's time to go.

how_know_if_dead.text:
[death:eyes_closed]I have a highly refined sense for when people die.
It's called 'Dead Reckoning'.
[death]I reckon you are dead.
[death:happy]Good name, right?

how_know_if_dead_2.text:
[death:eyes_closed]Anyway.  Your time has come.
[death:no_eyes]Allow me to escort you to the gates of hereafter.

play_tictactoe.text:
[death:angry]Really?
That's probably the worst possible game you could have chosen.
[death:eyes_closed]...
[death:no_eyes]So be it.

play_pong.text: [death:eyes_closed]I may be as old as time itself, but this does not mean I am unfamiliar with the latest in video gaming technology.  [death:no_eyes]Prepare yourself.

win_tictactoe.text:
[death:eyes_closed]Unsurprising.
[death:scared]Wait.  I lost?
What the hell?
[death:angry]That's impossible...  [death:bashful]I think?
[death]Or maybe not.
[death:no_eyes]Well played human.  What would you have me do with your soul?

lose_tictactoe.text:
[death:no_eyes]An inevitability, really.
Walk with me and I'll show you the path to the hereafter.  [death:eyes_closed]There's nothing left to be done.

win_pong.text:
[death:scared]That's impossible...
[death:eyes_closed]Seriously, that was great.
[death]A victory is a victory.  What would you have me do with your soul?

lose_pong.text:
[death:eyes_closed]Unsurprising.
[death]That's enough of this.  Time is infinite but my patience is not.  Let us depart.

draw_pong.text: [cat]How did you manage to _draw_ in pong?  That's seriously impossible!  I didn't even write this branch into the game!?

lots_to_finish.text: [death]Of course you have things left undone; the finality of death is the only pressure to which people are receptive.

not_right.text: [death:eyes_closed]Well you're really not in much of a position to argue.  Come with me or I'll leave you here to wander the umbral planes until your mind breaks and you're left as nothing but a ghoulish husk.
not_right.prompt: That's really not much of a choice I guess.

no_really.text:
[death:look_up]Ugh.  Fine.
[death:eyes_closed]What exactly is it that's so important?

true_love.text:
[death:angry]Ha ha.
Very funny.
That's actually hilarious.
Do you feel my sarcasm?
[death:eyes_closed]Against my better judgement, I will take you to the space beyond, but don't dilly dally.  We're leaving now.

im_scared.text: [death:eyes_closed]Little lamb, you almost nothing to fear any more.  Your pain is gone.  Your responsibilities are gone.  The only thing you have left to do is follow me.

almost_nothing_to_fear.text:
[death]Madness is a gift worse than death and more painful than pain itself.
Eternity wears on a mind, and even the most resilient minds break down eventually.
Come with me, or this is the fate that will befall you.

prefer_to_go_mad.text:
[death:eyes_closed]Suit yourself.
If you change your mind, 
[death]too bad.  I'm gone.

bring_to_heaven.text:
[death]I mean, I _can_ bring you to the gates of heaven, but they're not going to let you in.
They don't really let anybody in.
Also, I can't really recommend it.  It's full of self-righteous, self-important pricks who were convinced without evidence that they were right and now that they've gotten into the exclusive social club nothing will convince them they're wrong.
They don't want to help.  They want to look down on people.
If you're a compassionate soul, which you are, from the looks of it, might I recommend a nice seat at the fire?
It's generally pretty great if you don't break.

what_mean_break.text:
[death:bashful]...
[death]You know the saying, "The road to hell is paved with good intentions?"  Well I think you'll find it holds true in the pit.
People are optimistic for the first thousand years.  They see a world which, despite setbacks, is on an upward trend.  People are living longer.  Human rights are taking footholds across the world.
But there's always an end.  Humans can't beat thermodynamics, and sooner or later the game is over and the lights go out.
That weighs heavily on folks.
Knowing that everyone there is all that there will ever be?
[death:bashful]Well, eternity is a long time.[death:eyes_closed]
[death]A LONG time.
[death]And people can't handle it.  Out here in the umbral plane you'll go mad after a century.  In the pit, you might last longer, but eventually everyone falls apart.  At least there we have ways of setting your soul to rest.
What do you say?

rps_challenge.text: You dare challenge me to Rock, Paper, Scissors?  You will be destroyed.

play_mario_twins.text: [death]I don't think I've ever played Mario Twins.

[death]But after that you're coming with me.

[dog]Dog: *bark*
